,"1442":"1442","1526":"1526","Weston, Suffolk, England":"Weston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Norwich, , Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lapadge","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Fernand, Jacques, Serge.","Altered form of French   Lepage  , with the feminine definite article <i>la</i> instead of masculine <i>le</i> (a change that may have also been the result of the American English pronunciation)."],"variants":[{"name":"Lepage","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Marcel, Andre, Fernand, Pierre, Raoul, Adelard, Alcide, Christophe, Lucien, Normand, Adrien.","French: occupational or status name for a young servant, a variant of   Page   1, with fused masculine definite article <i>le</i>. Compare   Lapage  .","French Canadian: altered form of <b>Pagé</b> (see   Page   2)."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Lapadge was born in 1445, in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She married Nicholas Le Gris in 1465, in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1445–":"1445–Surnud","1442–1467":"1442–1467","1467–1526":"1467–1526","1445–Female":"1445–Surnud","1445":"1445","1467":"1467","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1526":"1526","Weston, Suffolk, England":"Weston, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norwich, , Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1445–":"1445–Kuollut","1442–1467":"1442–1467","1467–1526":"1467–1526","1445–Female":"1445–Kuollut","1445":"1445","1467":"1467","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1526":"1526","Weston, Suffolk, England":"Weston, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norwich, , Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1445–":"1445–Décédée","1442–1467":"1442–1467","1467–1526":"1467–1526","1445–Female":"1445–Décédée","1445":"1445","1467":"1467","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1526":"1526","Weston, Suffolk, England":"Weston, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Norwich, , Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Lapadge est née en 1445, à Norwich, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Nicholas Le Gris en 1465, à Norwich, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1445–":"1445–Verstorben","1442–1467":"1442–1467","1467–1526":"1467–1526","1445–Female":"1445–Verstorben","1445":"1445","1467":"1467","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1526":"1526","Weston, Suffolk, England":"Weston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Norwich, , Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England, U